  "prompt": "How early should I start ACT prep?",
  "response": "The ideal time to start ACT prep depends on several factors:\n\n1. Typical Recommendations:\n- Most students start preparing 3-6 months before their test date\n- Sophomore or early junior year is often recommended\n\n2. Factors to Consider:\n- Your current academic level\n- Target score\n- Available study time\n- Comfort with test material\n- Baseline diagnostic test score\n\n3. General Prep Timeline:\n- Start with a practice test to assess current level\n- Create a study plan\n- Begin light preparation 6-8 months before test\n- Intensify preparation 3-4 months before test\n- Do more intensive practice in final 2-3 months\n\n4. Preparation Strategies:\n- Take practice tests\n- Use study guides\n- Consider prep courses\n- Work on weak subject areas\n- Learn test-taking strategies\n\n5. When to Start:\n- If you're motivated and have time: Earlier is better\n- If you're busy: At least 3-4 months before test date\n- Consistent, spaced-out studying is more effective than cramming\n\nRemember, individual needs vary, so adjust this advice to your personal situation and learning style.",
